    "url": "/calendar/",
    "title": "Calendar",
    "body": "The 2019 Formula 1 season is contested over 21 Grand Prix held around the world. These include historic races such as the Monaco Grand Prix and the British Grand Prix but also new races such as the return of the French Grand Prix which was reintroduced in 2018. In the 2020 season, this will increase to with the introduction of the Dutch Grand Prix and the Vietnam Grand Prix. The next race is the 2019 Singapore Grand Prix held in Marina Bay, Singapore on the 22nd  of September. Below is the full calendar of races for the 2019 Formula 1 season:       Race       Date              Australian Grand Prix          17 Mar                Bahrain Grand Prix          31 Mar                Chinese Grand Prix          14 Apr                Azerbaijan Grand Prix          28 Apr                Spanish Grand Prix          12 May                Monaco Grand Prix          26 May                Canadian Grand Prix          09 Jun                French Grand Prix          23 Jun                Austrian Grand Prix          30 Jun                British Grand Prix          14 Jul                German Grand Prix          28 Jul                Hungarian Grand Prix          04 Aug                Belgian Grand Prix          01 Sep                Italian Grand Prix          08 Sep                Singapore Grand Prix          22 Sep                Russian Grand Prix          29 Sep                Japanese Grand Prix          13 Oct                Mexican Grand Prix          27 Oct                United States Grand Prix          03 Nov                Brazilian Grand Prix          17 Nov                Abu Dhabi Grand Prix          01 Dec      "
